varargs void add_living_thorns(int iRatio, string sMessage,int ibDamType)

This function will return damage to the Living's attacker.
iRatio is the sp:dam ratio, where the cost is dam / ratio in sp.
    The default ratio is 2.
sMessage is the message told to the Living. It is in room_message
    format. "$N1 $v1hurt $r1 on $p thorns." is the default.
ibDamType is the damage type that is returned. The default is
    WEAPON_PIERCE. The damage is not reduced by AC, but is reduced
    by resists.

eg. living->add_living_thorns();
    That would put everything in as the defaults.
eg. living->add_living_thorns(4);    
    That would make it 1 sp for every 4 damage, with the rest
    being the defaults.
eg. living->add_living_thorns(0,0,DAM_ACID);
    That would give the default ratio and message, but use
    DAM_ACID as the damage type.

Also:
  status query_living_thorns()
    returns 0/1 if living_thorns is active
  int query_living_thorns_ratio()
    returns the ratio set
  int query_living_thorns_damtype()
    returns the damage type set
  string query_living_thorns_message()
    returns the message set
